  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You and your eidolon form a beautiful symmetry when you engage in combat, becoming a formidable duo. When you or your eidolon successfully Strike a creature, you become synergized. This state of symbiosis is called @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-summoners-plus.misc.Item.H0W9EDjO1wwp38ty]{Synergy}, and you are either in a state of synergy or you are not. If you or your eidolon made a successful Strike as part of an activity, you do not gain Synergy until after you have completed the activity.</p><p>While you have synergy, you each gain a +5-foot status bonus to your Speed and if you are both adjacent to the same creature, that creature is off-guard to you and your eidolon.</p><p>Normally, you gain and use synergy only in combat encounters; when an encounter ends, you lose synergy.</p>"
    },
